when we push ourselves

09:35.232 --> 09:36.682
and do something
a little different.

09:36.683 --> 09:39.585
That's true, but if all the other teams
are doing amazing songs

09:39.586 --> 09:41.087
we're not going to be so good.

09:41.088 --> 09:42.622
You're right.
We're not going to be as good.

09:42.623 --> 09:43.840
We're going to be better.

09:43.841 --> 09:47.293
We won't be using
other people's words or music.

09:47.294 --> 09:48.711
It'll be our own.

09:48.712 --> 09:50.747
Our own heart, soul,
not just our voices.

09:50.748 --> 09:53.032
We have a really
talented songwriter

09:53.033 --> 09:55.551
in our midst. Rachel.

09:55.552 --> 09:57.920
I was thinking maybe you and I
could write a song together.

09:57.921 --> 09:59.538
I'm with Quinn and Rachel.

09:59.539 --> 10:01.824
I mean, if these two
can agree on something,

10:01.825 --> 10:02.975
it's probably an idea
worth considering.

10:02.976 --> 10:04.310
Wait, wait, so suddenly,

10:04.311 --> 10:06.429
you two are writing the music
for Regionals? No way.

10:06.430 --> 10:08.147
I think that everyone should
get a chance to write a song.

10:08.148 --> 10:09.565
Santana's right.
We can do this.

10:09.566 --> 10:11.317
What do you think,
Mr. Shue?

10:11.318 --> 10:14.087
I think we're doing original
songs for Regionals.

10:20.802 --> 10:22.469
Hey.

10:24.472 --> 10:26.691
Can I ask you a question?

10:26.692 --> 10:28.976
We used to be really close,
and I really miss being your friend.

10:28.977 --> 10:30.194
Still waiting for the question.

10:30.195 --> 10:32.446
- Did I do something wrong?
- No. Look, I don't know.

10:32.447 --> 10:33.915
Did you?

10:33.916 --> 10:35.816
All I know is you blew me off

10:35.817 --> 10:38.152
to be with
Stumbles McCripplepants.

10:38.153 --> 10:39.320
That's fine.

10:39.321 --> 10:40.872
It's your loss.

10:40.873 --> 10:42.423
'Cause now I get
the chance to write

10:42.424 --> 10:44.876
an awesome heterosexual
song about Sam

10:44.877 --> 10:46.511
that we're going
to sing at Regionals.

10:46.512 --> 10:47.845
Wait, you're still dating Sam?

10:47.846 --> 10:50.164
But you told me you
were in love with me.

10:50.165 --> 10:52.216
I honestly don't know
what I was thinking.

10:53.335 --> 10:54.552
Look, can you stop
staring at me?

10:54.553 --> 10:55.836
