my locker combo.

10:55.837 --> 10:57.805
Well, well.

10:57.806 --> 11:00.892
If it isn't Tweedle-Dumb
and Tweedle-Fake-Boobs.

11:00.893 --> 11:02.676
You know, you can't
talk to us like that.

11:02.677 --> 11:04.228
You're not our cheer
coach anymore.

11:04.229 --> 11:07.231
I'm not anybody's
cheer-leading coach anymore.

11:07.232 --> 11:09.683
You betrayed me,
and in case you haven't heard,

11:09.684 --> 11:11.035
I like to play dirty.

11:17.743 --> 11:19.627
I don't even remember
putting that in there.

11:21.046 --> 11:23.364
You know,
I think Blaine's version

11:23.365 --> 11:25.132
of the song is actually
better than the original.

11:25.133 --> 11:26.751
But it's not
in his natural key, so...

11:26.752 --> 11:29.470
- How dare you.
- Enough. I'm tired of this.

11:29.471 --> 11:30.755
I agree.
I think we should just

11:30.756 --> 11:32.206
let you pick the song
that you want to sing.

11:32.207 --> 11:35.526
No, I'm tired of the Warblers
being all about me.

11:35.527 --> 11:36.894
David, please make
sure everything

11:36.895 --> 11:38.596
I'm about to say goes down
in the official minutes.

11:38.597 --> 11:41.882
We are going to lose
at Regionals.

11:41.883 --> 11:44.268
- What?!
- I am incredibly grateful

11:44.269 --> 11:46.537
for the belief you've all given me,
as a junior member,

11:46.538 --> 11:48.055
to lead you all in these
wonderful songs this year.

11:48.056 --> 11:51.025
But, from what Kurt has told me
about New Directions,

11:51.026 --> 11:53.778
I just know I can't
beat them on my own.

11:53.779 --> 11:56.414
Which is why I propose
that we rearrange

11:56.415 --> 11:59.233
our 11:00 number
and turn it into a duet.

12:00.535 --> 12:02.236
To showcase other
talent in this group.

12:02.237 --> 12:03.170
Why don't we just
play it on kazoos?

12:03.171 --> 12:04.338
Point of order! Point of order!

12:04.339 --> 12:06.841
Now, we all lost one
of our own this week.

12:06.842 --> 12:08.342
Pavarotti's voice was
silenced by death,

12:08.343 --> 12:12.463
and I don't want to silence
anyone else's voices in this group.

12:12.464 --> 12:14.465
I think Pavarotti
would roll over

12:14.466 --> 12:15.600
in his tiny, tiny,
little grave.

12:15.601 --> 12:17.802
The placement of which
has yet to be determined.

12:17.803 --> 12:19.253
All right, a vote.

12:19.254 --> 12:21.772
